    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-07-15T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-07-15T17:00:00-05:00" n="341"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d341">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/2241</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in China</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MJVA1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-07-15T18:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 15, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Yours July 9, 4 p.m.<note n="3" xml:id="d341fn3">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_271">p. 271</ref>.</note> If
                    proposed movement of Czecho-Slovak troops takes place their starting point and
                    destination will both be in Russian territory. They will pass through the
                    railway zone of the Chinese Eastern Railway which is a Russian railway. Their
                    sole purpose is to rescue their comrades from the menace of armed German and
                    Austrian prisoners now bringing the war into Siberia. The Czecho-Slovaks were
                    organized to fight the Central powers. <pb facs="0374" n="284" xml:id="pg_284"/>
                    This Government believes that no exception can be taken to assisting them and
                    accordingly desires that the acquiescence and approval of the Chinese Government
                    be sought so that they can pass over the Chinese Eastern Railway if such a
                    movement becomes necessary.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PFL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
